Source: vitos-sso
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Dr. Hemraj Shobharam Lamkuche <vitbhopal.os@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: vitos-sso
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, vitos-base, vitos-monitor,
 freeipa-client, sssd, sssd-ipa, libpam-sss, libnss-sss,
 oddjob-mkhomedir
Description: VITOS FreeIPA / LDAP single sign-on
 Joins the lab workstation to a FreeIPA realm and chains pam_sss into
 /etc/pam.d/common-auth so VIT credentials authenticate every shell, ssh,
 sudo, and dashboard login. On first successful join the v1 hardcoded
 'admin' and 'student' accounts are deleted; their home directories are
 archived under /var/lib/vitos/legacy-homes/ rather than destroyed.
 Configuration is read from /etc/vitos/sso.toml; the package fail-soft
 leaves the system fully usable in v1 mode if no sso.toml is staged.
